findingsText:
 The research funded by this grant has shown:
1. That there is a lack of awareness of biosecurity risks among scientists and technologists in university and in industry;
2. There is widespread lack of recognition by scientists and technologists as to their personal and corporate responsibilities under the Biological and Toxin Weapons Convention and under the Chemical Weapons Convention, not to carry out or allow work that may pose any public threat under the definitions of these treaties;
3. That it is possible, through the production of tailored educational materials, to address this lack of awareness and to equip scientists and technologists with a skill set and competencies that enable them to meet these responsibilities;
4. That it is possible to work nationally and internationally to promote and enhance biosecurity capacities and competencies through these educational approaches. All of our educational materials are available free online for download. They can be used as they are or altered to suit specific needs. Many are in foreign languages. Aerospace, Defence and Marine,Agriculture, Food and Drink,Chemicals,Communities and Social Services/Policy,Education,Environment,Healthcare,Government, Democracy and Justice,Manufacturing, including Industrial Biotechology,Pharmaceuticals and Medical Biotechnology,Security and Diplomacy
